 :cuspy: /kuhsÂ´pee/, adj. [WPI: from the {DEC} abbreviation CUSP, for
`Commonly Used System Program', i.e., a utility program used by many people.
Now rare.] 1. (of a program) Well-written. 2. Functionally excellent. A
program that performs well and interfaces well to users is cuspy. Oppose
{rude}. 3. [NYU] Said of an attractive woman, especially one regarded as
available. Implies a certain curvaceousness.